comments.en: This is the Materials Design Ontology.

comment.en: A computational method is a way to process structures and/or properties into output structures and/or calculated properties.
A computational method parameter is a parameter used in a computational method.
A Hartree Fock method is a computational quantum mechanical modelling method used to investigate the electronic structure based on variational search over wave functions.
A length triple defines the three parameters (a, b, c) that represent the lengths in three axes respectively.
An occupancy ties a specific species to a site.

seeAlso.value: International Tables for Crystallography, Volume A, Fourth, revised edition, Section 8.1.5.

comment.en: A group of linear mappings of vector space, which is corresonpond to the group of motions in point space determining the symmetry of the macroscopic crystal, is called the point group of the crystal, furthermore of the crystal structure, and is also called the point group of its space group.

seeAlso.value: A GeneralizedGradientApproximation is a classification of exchange correlation energy functionals that only use the local value of the electronic density and its gradient.

comment.en: A lattice defines a peroidic arrangement of one or more atoms.
A reference agent is the representation of the reference that the structure or property refer to.
A physical property is an objective property over a physical system. (ie, a property pertains to the physical reality)
A basis defines a spatial unit used to express fractional coordinates.
A calculation is the use of a specific computational method to process structures and/or properties into output structures and/or calculated properties.
A site is a point in a lattice.

seeAlso.value: A hybrid meta generalized gradient approximation is a classification of exchange correlation energy functionals that combine exact exchange from Hartree–Fock theory with meta generalized gradient approximation.

comment.en: A composition is used to represent what chemical elements composing a structure and the ratio of the chemical elements.
A coordinate vector is the coordinates of a point in space.
A calculated property is a proprty that is a result from a calculation.
A structure is the information of the sites and their occupancies in a material or materials system.

seeAlso.value: A metaGeneralizedGradientApproximation is a classification of exchange correlation energy functionals that only use the local value of the electronic density and its gradient and the Kohn–Sham orbital kinetic energy density.

comment.en: A property in materials design is data pertaining to at least one material or materials system.

seeAlso.value: International Tables for Crystallography, Volume !, Fourth, revised edition, Section 8.1.5.

comment.en: A space group is the symmetry group of a three-dimensional crystal pattern is called its space group.

seeAlso.value: A hybrid generalized gradient approximation is a classification of exchange correlation energy functionals that combine exact exchange from Hartree–Fock theory with generalized gradient approximation.

comment.en: A hybrid functional is a classification of exchange correlation energy functionals that combine exact exchange from HartreeFock theory with another exchange correlation energy approximation.
A DFT method is a computational quantum mechanical modelling method used to investigate the electronic structure based on optimization of the energy over electronic densities.

seeAlso.value: An LDA is a classification of exchange correlation energy functionals that only use the local value of the electronic density.

comment.en: A angle triple is a vector of three angles which represent the angles among three bases in a cell.
A species is the combination of atoms on each site.

seeAlso.value: An ExchangeCorrelationEnergyFunctional is a functional to compute the exchange correlation energy.

comment.en: An axis-vectors is the three vectors which represent the bases of cell.
